wikipedia_page.main: Alec Higgins (birth registered fourth ¼ 1908 – third ¼ 1965) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1920s, 1930s and 1940s. He played at representative level for Great Britain, England, British Empire and Lancashire, and at club level for Widnes, as a centre, prop, second-row, or  loose forward, i.e. number 3 or 4, or, 8 or 10, during the era of contested scrums.
